commit.message: Renamed "master" to "main" in issue template
Version bump v0.15.0
Update docs with correct cursor module
Added test case of shared connection across threads/loops

Support accessing Connection from multiple event loops

This changes the connection object to stop using the `loop` argument
passed to it at creation in favor of creating futures from whatever
event loop is the current loop at the time of executing a query.
To support Python 3.6, which does not have `Future.get_loop()`, this
adds a simple helper function that will use the `Future._loop` value
when necessary.

This deprecates the `loop` parameter to the Connection constructor
and the `connect()` helper. Deprecation warnings will be generated
when passing a `loop` parameter to either one.
Fix type annotations and base classes for @contextmanager results
Break cursors out into separate module
Ignore duplicate bases and cyclic imports (type checking)
Version bump v0.14.1
